 4.6. Factor 6: household access to (set of machines) 
 This factor represents the degree to which families have access to services as pointed to/showed by the strong 
 loadings on water (0.46), sewage (0.75), bathrooms 
 (0.72) and telephone (0.48) access. Families positively connected with this factor also tend to have a 
 lower share of people/of the group speaking an native (to) 
 language and lower (related to surrounding conditions or the health of the Earth) problems. This partially<p><strong>NOTE: This document is incomplete. It was shortened to the maximum document length of 50,000 characters.</strong></p><div style="clear:both">&nbsp;</div>
